sequenceDiagram
    participant Dev1 as Developer A<br/>terraform apply
    participant Dev2 as Developer B<br/>terraform apply
    participant S3 as S3 State Bucket<br/>agora-terraform-state
    participant DDB as DynamoDB Lock Table<br/>terraform-lock
    participant CW as CloudWatch Alarm<br/>Stale Lock Detection
    participant SNS as SNS Topic<br/>#dr-alerts

    Note over Dev1,Dev2: Normal operation — serialized access

    Dev1->>DDB: Acquire lock (ConditionalPut LockID)
    DDB-->>Dev1: ✅ Lock acquired (version X)
    Dev1->>S3: Read terraform.tfstate
    S3-->>Dev1: State v5

    Dev2->>DDB: Acquire lock (ConditionalPut LockID)
    DDB-->>Dev2: ❌ ConditionalCheckFailed (locked by Dev1)

    Dev1->>S3: Write new state v6
    Dev1->>DDB: Release lock (DeleteItem)

    Dev2->>DDB: Acquire lock (ConditionalPut LockID)
    DDB-->>Dev2: ✅ Lock acquired (version X+1)
    Dev2->>S3: Read terraform.tfstate v6
    S3-->>Dev2: State v6 (latest)

    Note over Dev2,CW: Stale lock scenario — runaway

    Dev2->>S3: Write state v7 (timeout 💥)
    Note over Dev2: Process crashes before release
    Dev2-->>DDB: ❌ Lock still held (stale!)

    Dev1->>DDB: Acquire lock (ConditionalPut LockID)
    DDB-->>Dev1: ❌ ConditionalCheckFailed (stale lock)

    Dev1->>DDB: Describe table → check LockID age
    DDB-->>Dev1: Lock held for 15min (stale!)

    DDB-->>CW: ConditionalCheckFailedRequests > 50
    CW-->>SNS: 🚨 Stale lock detected!

    Note over Dev1,SNS: Recovery — force unlock

    Dev1->>DDB: Force delete stale lock
    Dev1->>S3: Check state serial
    S3-->>Dev1: State v6 (incomplete write)
    Dev1->>S3: Push restored state
    Dev1->>DDB: Acquire lock (fresh)
    DDB-->>Dev1: ✅ Lock acquired
    Dev1->>S3: Read state v6 (recovered)
